# Component & Form Patterns

## Creating a shadcn/ui Component

All shared UI components live in `src/shared/components/ui/` and follow this pattern:

```tsx
import { cva, type VariantProps } from 'class-variance-authority';
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils.ts';

const myComponentVariants = cva(
  'base-classes-here',
  {
    variants: {
      variant: { default: '...', secondary: '...' },
      size: { default: '...', sm: '...', lg: '...' },
    },
    defaultVariants: { variant: 'default', size: 'default' },
  },
);

function MyComponent({
  className,
  variant,
  size,
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<'div'> & VariantProps<typeof myComponentVariants>) {
  return (
    <div
      data-slot="my-component"
      className={cn(myComponentVariants({ variant, size, className }))}
      {...props}
    />
  );
}

export { MyComponent, myComponentVariants };
```

Key rules:
- Use **plain functions** (not `React.forwardRef`) — React 19 forwards refs automatically (exceptions: `ui/input.tsx` + `ui/textarea.tsx` keep `forwardRef` for react-hook-form `register()`)
- Add `data-slot` attribute for styling hooks
- Import from `radix-ui` monorepo (not individual `@radix-ui/react-*` packages)
- Always accept and merge `className` via `cn()`
- Export both the component and its variants

## Creating a Form with Validation

Forms use react-hook-form + zod + shadcn/ui components:

```tsx
import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';
import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';
import { mySchema, type MyInput } from './contracts.ts';
import { Button } from '@/shared/components/ui/button.tsx';
import { Input } from '@/shared/components/ui/input.tsx';
import { Label } from '@/shared/components/ui/label.tsx';
import { FormError } from '@/shared/forms/FormError/index.ts';

function MyForm() {
  const {
    register,
    handleSubmit,
    formState: { errors, isSubmitting },
  } = useForm<MyInput>({
    resolver: zodResolver(mySchema),
    defaultValues: { field: '' },
  });

  const onSubmit = async (data: MyInput) => {
    // Call API via TanStack mutation, never raw fetch
  };

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>
      <FormError message={apiError} />
      <Label htmlFor="field">Field</Label>
      <Input {...register('field')} aria-invalid={!!errors.field} />
      {errors.field && (
        <p className="text-xs text-destructive" role="alert">
          {errors.field.message}
        </p>
      )}
      <Button type="submit" isLoading={isSubmitting}>
        Submit
      </Button>
    </form>
  );
}
```

Key rules:
- Zod schema is the single source of truth (defined in `contracts.ts`)
- Always use `aria-invalid` on invalid inputs
- Always use `role="alert"` on error messages
- Use Button's `isLoading` prop during submission

## Creating a Page Contracts File

```ts
import { z } from 'zod';

// Define the full entity schema
export const entitySchema = z.object({
  id: z.string().uuid(),
  name: z.string().min(1, 'Name is required'),
  status: z.enum(['active', 'inactive']),
  createdAt: z.string(),
});

export type Entity = z.infer<typeof entitySchema>;

// Define input schemas (omit server-generated fields)
export const createEntitySchema = entitySchema.omit({
  id: true,
  createdAt: true,
});

export type CreateEntityInput = z.infer<typeof createEntitySchema>;
```

## Creating a Page Route Module

```tsx
// src/pages/<name>/<name>.route.tsx — Component only
import { MyPage } from './MyPage.tsx';

export function Component() {
  return <MyPage />;
}
```

Register access in `src/app/routes/routeTree.tsx` (`beforeLoad` + `gatewayFromManifest(manifest)`).
See `agent-os/skills/routing-tenancy/SKILL.md`.

## Auth Method Buttons (`/login`)

Never hand-roll loading/disable logic for a sign-in method button. Every method on the unified
auth screen — OAuth providers, passkey, email send/verify — renders through the shared
`AuthMethodButton` (`src/shared/forms/AuthForm/components/AuthMethodButton/`) so they behave
identically. Adding a new method = one more `<AuthMethodButton>` with its `target`, `label`, `icon`,
`onClick`, and (if it needs a captcha token) `captchaGated`.

```tsx
<AuthMethodButton
  target={{ method: 'oauth', provider }}
  pending={pending}                 // the single in-flight action (AuthContinuePending | null)
  captchaGated                      // OAuth + email need a Turnstile token; passkey does not
  turnstileReady={turnstileReady}
  icon={<ProviderIcon provider={provider} />}
  label={t(AUTH_KEYS.auth.continueWithProvider, { provider })}
  onClick={() => void startOAuth(provider)}
  extraDisabled={/* form/cooldown/code-length conditions only */}
  testId={providerTestId(provider)}
/>
```

Guarantees enforced by the component (do not re-derive these inline):

- **Stable label** — text never swaps to "…ing" while loading; the spinner is the only cue.
- **One spinner at a time** — only the clicked method spins; the rest disable without a spinner.
- **Per-method captcha** — `captchaGated` buttons show the token-minting spinner **only when
  nothing else is pending** (the Turnstile token is single-use; without the guard one click spins
  every OAuth button).

Cross-method predicates live in `auth-form-pending.ts` (`authMethodIsLoading` /
`authMethodIsDisabled` / `authEmailPanelIsBlocked`); non-button surfaces (inputs, links) reuse them.
Full spec: `docs/reference/unified-auth-flows.md` → "Method button states".

## Animation Patterns

Use the animation kit from `@/lib/animations/` (everything here respects
`prefers-reduced-motion`):

- `PageTransition` — route-level enter transition.
- `Skeleton` / `SkeletonShimmer` — loading placeholders.
- `useAnimeCountUp` — Anime.js number count-up (dashboard stats).
- `prefersReducedMotion` — gate custom motion on the user's setting.

Richer motion (dashboard, onboarding steps) is built with Anime.js (`animejs`) —
see the `animejs` skill.

## React Performance (Vite SPA)

This project uses **React 19 + Vite + TanStack Router** (not Next.js). Apply these patterns in `src/**/*.tsx`:

- **Code splitting:** Routes are lazy-loaded via `<page>.route.tsx` and `routeTree.tsx`; use `React.lazy` for heavy page-specific UI when needed.
- **Server state:** Use TanStack Query hooks in `pages/<name>/hooks/` — not `useEffect` + manual fetch.
- **RBAC pre-checks:** Enforce in `routeTree.tsx` `beforeLoad` via `gatewayFromManifest(manifest)` before the page renders — never in a route `loader` (see route module pattern above).
- **Local state:** Keep UI state local; use react-hook-form for forms; Zustand only for theme/UI (see `project-conventions.mdc`).
- **Derived state:** Prefer computing values during render over duplicating state in `useEffect`.
- **Memoization:** Default to no `memo` / `useMemo` / `useCallback` unless profiling shows a benefit.
- **Loading / error / empty:** Handle `isPending`, `isError`, and empty data in page components — never leave ambiguous blank screens.
- **Bundle size:** Import shadcn primitives from `@/shared/components/ui/`; avoid barrel re-exports in pages; do not add dependencies without justification (see `engineering-principles.mdc`).
